gwt.material.design.client.data

Interface DataView<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HasCategories, HasColumns<T>, HasDataSource<T>, com.google.gwt.event.shared.HasHandlers, com.google.gwt.view.client.HasKeyProvider<T>, HasRenderer<T>, HasRows<T>, ViewSettings
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataView, InfiniteDataView, StandardDataView

    public interface DataView<T>
extends HasRows<T>, HasColumns<T>, HasDataSource<T>, HasRenderer<T>, com.google.gwt.view.client.HasKeyProvider<T>, HasCategories, ViewSettings
    A data view is in charge of rendering the data within the data table.
    Author:
    Ben Dol
